dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Hey, you guys! Look what I found! Look at this!  That’s my Mom’s writing! Look.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Me and Frank and Phoebe, Graduation 1965.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Y'know what that means?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: That you’re actually 50?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: No-no, that’s not, that’s not me Phoebe, that’s her pal Phoebe. According to her high school yearbook, they were like B.F.F. Best Friends Forever.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 4
dialog.text: Speaker 4: Oh!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 5
dialog.text: Speaker 5: That is so cool.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: I know! So this woman probably could like have all kinds of stories about my parents, and she might even know like where my Dad is. So I looked her up, and she lives out by the beach. So maybe this weekend we could go to the beach?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 4
dialog.text: Speaker 4: Yeah! Yeah, we can!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 6
dialog.text: Speaker 6: Shoot! I can’t go, I have to work!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 7
dialog.text: Speaker 7: That’s too bad.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 5
dialog.text: Speaker 5: Ohh, big, fat bummerrr.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: So great! Okay! Tomorrow we’re gonna drive out to Montauk.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Hi, Ursula.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Hey!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Okay, well umm, I know that we haven’t talked in a long time, but umm okay, our Mom is not our birth Mom. This-this other lady is our birth Mom.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Right, okay, the one that lives in Montuak, umm-hmm.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: You know her?!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: No, I umm, I read about her in Mom’s suicide note.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: There-there was a suicide note?! Well, do you still have it?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Hang on.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: I can’t believe you didn’t tell me there was a suicide note!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Yeah. So how have you been doing?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: I, umm, shut up!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: “Good-bye Phoebe and Ursula. I’ll miss you. P.S. Your Mom lives in Montauk.” You just wrote this!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Well, it’s pretty much the gist. Well, except for the poem. You read the poem, right?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Noooo!!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: All right, hang on!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Hey guys!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Hey!!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: Oh my God! It’s Joey Tribbiani of Mac and C.H.E.E.S.E.!!!!!!!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Oh that’s right. It’s your first day! So are you psyched to fight fake crime with your robot sidekick?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Am I psyched? The lead in my own TV series? I’ve dreamed about this for years! Why have I not been preparing?!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 4
dialog.text: Speaker 4: No! Joey, you’re going to be great!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: But I got to act with a robot Pheebs, and-and I don’t know anything about technology! I can’t even use Chandler’s computer except to find porn! And-and that’s only ‘cause it’s right there when you turn it on!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 5
dialog.text: Speaker 5: I think our lover’s spat will start a little early this month.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 4
dialog.text: Speaker 4: I’ll be waiting.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Lucky bastard! Janice.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: How are you Ms. Hot Shot chef with the big fancy restaurant with the best chicken ever!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: I’m fine.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Ohh! What is that on your finger?! I’m blind!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Oh… Uh…

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: So, who’s the lucky guy?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: OH…MY…GAWD! I am so sorry sweetie, are you okay? You didn’t tell her we were getting married, did you?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Well, she saw the ring.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: Did she freak out?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Well, she was shocked when I told her, but then again so were most people.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: Right.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Well, she actually has a boyfriend y’know herself, named Clark. Uh, she also kinda invited herself to our wedding. Clark too.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: You said no right?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Huh?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: You said no right?!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Well, she corned me! She asked if the wedding was in town! I mean, what was I supposed to do?!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: Lie!!! How hard is that?! The check’s in the mail! Oh your baby is so cute! I can’t wait to read your book Ross!!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Come on! So she comes to the wedding! I mean it won’t be so bad.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: What do you think she’s just gonna sit there quietly? You don’t think she’s gonna want to make a toast? You don’t think she’s gonna want to grab the microphone and sing Part-time Lover?!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Oh my God, she’s not gonna like the chicken that night either is she?!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: Y’know what? It’s gonna be okay. Y’know what? She’s probably not gonna even want to come.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Really?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: No! That was a lie! See how easy that was?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: So-so you would’ve just lied?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: Yes!!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Would it really have been that easy?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: Yes!!!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Good, so do it Saturday night because we’re going to dinner with her and Clark.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Hey, you should really read that book you wrote. Wow! You saw the hat in the kitchen and knew that she'd have to go in there hatless to get it. You can have your own health inspector detective show!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Oh, I don't know about that.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Yeah, but then I can be you sidekick Vunda.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Maybe uh, Vunda could give me her number and I can ask her to dinner sometime.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Okay, she would love that! Y'know, 'cause you know all the clean places to eat.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: I-I'll call ya.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Okay.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Sweetie okay. It’s okay. Everybody made it to the wedding. I’m fine.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Kinda hurtin’ my hand though.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: I know.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Well it wasn't that many guys. I mean, if you consider how many guys there actually are, it's a very small percentage.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Hey, it's not that big a deal, I was just curious.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: G'night.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 4
dialog.text: Speaker 4: Night Richard. Good luck Mon.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Alright, before I tell you, uh, why don't you tell me how many women you've been with.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 4
dialog.text: Speaker 4: Two.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Two? TWO? How is that possible? I mean, have you seen you?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 4
dialog.text: Speaker 4: Well, I mean what can I say? I, I was married to Barbara for 30 years. She was my high school sweetheart, now you, that's two.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Two it is. Ok, time for bed, I'm gonna go brush my teeth.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 4
dialog.text: Speaker 4: Woah, woah, no wait a minute now. C'mon it's your turn. Oh c'mon. Ya know, I don't need the actual number, just a ballpark.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Ok, it is definitely less than a ballpark.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Oh my God! I can’t believe my little brother is married!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Oh I know!!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: You guys, why didn’t you tell me you were eloping?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: ‘Cause it just sorta happened, y’know we were at the courthouse, we were having lunch…

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Wait, wait, why were you at the courthouse?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: We were having lunch. Yeah and then all of the sudden we were like, "Hey! Y'know, we’re here, having lunch let’s get married!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Wow, a year and a half ago I didn’t even know I had a brother, and now I have a sister too. Okay. Okay. Stop it, don’t. So, I gotta get you a gift now. Is there anything you need?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Uhh, yeah.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: We’ve been trying to get pregnant, uh pretty much ever since we got engaged, we thought we’d get a jump on things, y’know no one’s getting any younger.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: See the thing is umm, we’re not able to y’know, uh, conceive.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 3
dialog.text: Speaker 3: And we’ve tried everything, we’ve seen a bunch of doctors.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: A new place for a new Ross. I'm gonna have you and all the guys from work over once it's y'know, furnished.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: I must say it's nice to see you back on your feet.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Well I am that. And that whole rage thing is definitely behind me.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: I wonder if its time for you to rejoin our team at the museum?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Oh Donald that-that would be great. I am totally ready to come back to work. I—What? No! Wh… What are you doing?!!  GET OFF MY SISTER!!!!!!!!!!!!!

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Hi.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Schnoodle. Oh my God, what the hell happened to my dog?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: It was an accident, and, and the woman who did this would never ever hurt a dog on purpose. She's a vegetarian.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: What are these, stitches?

dialog.speaker: Speaker 1
dialog.text: Speaker 1: Yeah, eight of them. That's 56 to him. You know also, if, if it's raining, you can't let him look up too long 'cause that cone'll fill up really really fast.

dialog.speaker: Speaker 2
dialog.text: Speaker 2: Yeah well, thanks for bringing back what's left of him.
